I used to make so many other montages in the past, and some of the most important moments aren’t here in video form, but here are some sweet clips from the past year ✨

It’s my mom’s birthday. If you know me, you know she’s forever the most important person in my life. I’m convinced I probably would’ve ended up a bitter, cold person if I had anyone else instead. She has taught me to be brave, that loss and hard things are just a normal part of life, and to love the underdog. She taught me to be loving and show up for people (and any animal that crosses our paths). We hold each other’s secrets and hands whenever possible. We truly are a team in this weird life and I love her too much. 
If my mom has ever hugged you, go tell her happy birthday.

slime time baybeeee

I’ve been slowly sinking into an actual break from creative endeavors and advocacy. I’ve been thinking about what breaks mean and how to rest when momentum halting feels like premature loss of something ahead. But alas, my body and mind have conspired against me to pause as long as it takes to rid of this burnout and beyond. I’m not going anywhere, but even with the few recent ideas I’ve had I don’t exactly know what’s next or when or how. For now I am just waiting for boredom to find me but so far it’s just been me trying to breathe and sleep and eat and work and hang and clean and nest and heal and talk and hold and —
Do my fucking taxes. 

Ps - If you haven’t gotten a book, there are still some left waiting to go home with you. Just message me and I’ll respond even in hibernation. Stay warm y’all. Lmk any tips on your experiences with rest or burnout, seriously. 🤘🏼

Looking back at a lot of things lately. What I thought would be a rest period of a few months has turned into a year of keeping afloat and creativity rarely within reach. Still don’t know what things I’ll find when it finally is found again more sustainably. 

Until then, I’m thinking about hands again, and grateful for the days y’all helped me to be brave on display. 🧡

Finally accepting I need some support with finding more stability before the winter months.
I've been very stubborn about asking for help per usual
- especially since so many others need help these days too. But the past 6 months have been consistently piling up and making my physical/mental health worse.

Internalized ableism is a bitch. Repeated temporary housing/makeshift moves with a lot of needs during escalating rent prices is even worse.

Link in bio. ❤️‍🩹
